    "verified": true,
    "about": "Andrea is a Member of Technical Staff at Thinking Machines Lab. Previously, he was a Research Scientist at Meta’s Fundamental AI Research (FAIR), where he focused on multimodal language models and LLM-based agents capable of navigating user interfaces to accomplish user goals.\n\nAndrea earned his doctorate in Electronic & Computer Engineering from The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology (HKUST). He was honored with the Outstanding Paper Award at ACL 2019 and received the Best Paper Award at the NeurIPS 2019 ConvAI Workshop.\n\nHis research has been featured in prominent outlets such as MIT Technology Review and VentureBeat, highlighting its broader impact on the AI and technology landscape.\n\nBeyond his research contributions, Andrea is actively involved in the academic community. He has served as a program committee member and reviewer for leading machine learning and natural language processing conferences, including ACL, EMNLP, NeurIPS, ICML, ICLR, and AAAI. He has also contributed as a reviewer to journals such as the Journal of Natural Language Engineering and Computer Speech & Language. In addition, Andrea co-presented a tutorial on Deeper Conversational AI at NeurIPS 2020.",
